<div class="install-process-step">
	Installation Progress: Step 2 of 5
</div>
<div class="clear"></div>

<h3 class="text-center">Database Configuration</h3>
<div class="clear"></div>

<div class="explanation text-medium bump-down-most">
	BeansBooks will automatically configure your database. Before proceeding, create your database and database user. 
	If you need assistance, check the README.md file for step by step database and database user creation instructions.
</div>

<form action="" method="POST">
	<input type="hidden" name="install-step" value="2">

	<div class="explanation form text-medium bump-down-most">
		<div class="text-medium">Please enter your MySQL database details.</div>

        <div class="left-right-row bump-down-more">
            <span class="left">Database Type</span>
            <span class="right">
                <select name="type">
                    {{#db_types}}
                        <option value="{{value}}">{{title}}</option>
                    {{/db_types}}
                </select>
            </span>
        </div>
        
		<div class="left-right-row bump-down-more">
			<span class="left">Hostname</span>
			<span class="right"><input type="text" name="database_hostname" placeholder="i.e. localhost or 192.168.0.1:1337" value=""></span>
		</div>

		<div class="left-right-row bump-down-more">
			<span class="left">Database Name</span>
			<span class="right"><input type="text" name="database_database" placeholder="i.e. beans" value=""></span>
		</div>

		<div class="left-right-row bump-down-more">
			<span class="left">Username</span>
			<span class="right"><input type="text" name="database_username" placeholder="" value=""></span>
		</div>

		<div class="left-right-row bump-down-more">
			<span class="left">Password</span>
			<span class="right"><input type="password" name="database_password" placeholder="" value=""></span>
		</div>

	</div>

	<div class="explanation text-small bump-down-most">
		<span class="text-bold">Database Creation:</span> The README.md file has a section titled &quot;MySQL&quot;
		that provides instructions on how to create a database and user account for BeansBooks.
	</div>

	<div class="explanation text-center bump-down-most">
		<a href="#" class="button process-step">Verify Database Information</a>
	</div>
</form>
